1️⃣ Your understanding (in simple words)

👉 POSTMapping

Data comes from client (Postman)
JSON → converted to Java Object
Saved in server database
Response sent back to client

👉 GETMapping

Data is read from database
Returned to client (Postman)
So your sentence is correct 👇
When data comes from client using Postman, @PostMapping creates/saves it on the server, and @GetMapping reads and returns it to the client.

